<h2>Key Sleep Peptides</h2>

<h3>DSIP: The Delta Sleep Trigger</h3>

<p>Delta sleep-inducing peptide was first isolated in 1977 from rabbit brain tissue during electrically induced sleep. It's a nine-amino-acid neuropeptide that promotes the slow-wave (delta) stages of sleep without causing morning grogginess.</p>

<p>A 2025 clinical study showed <strong>40% improvement in sleep continuity</strong> among participants using DSIP, with increases of up to 25% in stage 3 and 4 sleep duration (<a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/3544903/">Graf &amp; Kastin, 1986</a>).</p>

