  <p style="font-size:14px;margin-bottom:8px;"><strong>Administration:</strong> Subcutaneous injection, 30 min before bed</p>
  <p style="font-size:14px;margin-bottom:8px;"><strong>Typical dose:</strong> 100&ndash;200 mcg, 3&ndash;5 nights per week</p>
  <p style="font-size:14px;margin-bottom:0;"><strong>Best for:</strong> People who can't reach or maintain deep sleep stages</p>
</div>

<p><a href="/articles/dsip-sleep-peptide-guide">DSIP</a> shows particular promise for shift workers who need to reset disrupted sleep patterns. Unlike benzodiazepines, it doesn't suppress REM sleep or cause rebound insomnia when discontinued.</p>

