<p>Clinical trials have shown this combination increases slow-wave sleep by over 20%. That's the most restorative sleep phase, responsible for tissue repair, immune function, and memory consolidation (<a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16352683/">Copinschi et al., 2005</a>).</p>

