<p>The connection between gut health and sleep quality is well established. Your gut produces roughly 90% of the body's serotonin, which converts to melatonin. <a href="/articles/bpc-157-complete-guide">BPC-157</a> is a 15-amino-acid peptide derived from human gastric juice that helps repair gut lining and reduce intestinal inflammation.</p>

<p>When gut inflammation reduces serotonin production, melatonin output drops too. BPC-157 addresses this root cause by restoring gut barrier integrity and modulating the gut-brain axis (<a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/29300334/">Sikiric et al., 2018</a>).</p>

