<p>KPV (Lysine-Proline-Valine) is a tripeptide fragment of alpha-MSH that reduces systemic inflammation through melanocortin receptors. Chronic inflammation disrupts sleep architecture and is a major driver of nighttime awakenings.</p>

<p>By calming inflammatory responses, <a href="/articles/kpv-peptide-guide">KPV</a> helps people who wake from discomfort or pain during the night. It's especially relevant for those with autoimmune conditions or chronic inflammatory states.</p>

